Comment:
I am a HUGE Marvel and Robert DOwney Jr. Fan and form what I have heard: Captain America's shield can ONLY be broken by VERY few things, such as Ultron. No, Ultron is not J.A.R.V.I.S turned evil that got out of Tony's hands because in the last Iron Man, JARVIS was destroyed in the house collapse and was taken away by Tony (most likely to a dump or city college ;). I believe Captain America will be killed off (sorry to those Chris Evans fans out there) but Chris will be returning in Fantastic Four, coming soon, as Human Torch. Cap will be replaced not with the winter soldier but with Falcon, to add more african american actors into the Avengers. Thor might also become female in the next avengers, to include more girls. As for Ultron himself, he was (in this movie) a creation from Tony, that went terribly wrong: hence there are no strings on me, saying Tony cant control him like he does his suits. As for the rock awesome Iron Man suit that is pretty bad ass, Tony can still power his suits with no arc reactor. Heck, he is a tech genius, and has money and science on his side. I dont know much about Hulk, but I think he will be in the state of severe injury throughout the movie. I love the Avengers, escpacially you ROBERT DOWNEY JR, (if ur out there, u are my real life hero and im ur biggest fan) and Marvel Comics. Hope this helped. Thoughts?
-Marvel Geek ;P

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
I hope the sound quality to Ultron is better in final film. It sounds Garbled and awful, like Hardy's Bane. Spader is a charismatic actor with a low, graveled voice. You have to hit the pitches right or it sounds like feedback.

It looks like some elements of this movie will be lead ins to Captain America 3: Civil War. Should be interesting. And I appreciate that Vision was left out of the trailer. We know too much already I think.

And there is no reason for DC/Marvel love/hate anymore. This is ridiculous banter. DC is catching up to the reinvention that Marvel products started back with Blade in the theaters. It was an independent project then, but Blade set the standard for comic involvement in cinema in the next century for all of these comic companies.

If you want to match up the two companies, both have had ups and downs in their pics and now Marvel has hit their stride with their major movie franchises (Iron Man, Thor & Captain America) and it is picking up steam with SHIELD and perhaps will generate a new market with Netflix's "Marvel Knights" features. DC, with any luck will come into its own with "Dawn of Justice" having made stellar numbers with the "Dark Knight" franchise and the "Man of Steel" but was by far the bigger small screen presence with Smallville, however it has had its flops too before striking it big with "Arrow" and "Gotham".

Absurd to get into this Team Marvel v. Team DC sort of thing. I hope for great adaptations from both companies because I grew up with both.

Besides, I want to see a conclusion to Hellboy and a revisit to League of Extraordinary Gentlemen. Give me more fringe stuff like "Invincible" or "Savage Dragon".

Comment:
Don't get me wrong, i loved the trailer, but i'm a little afraid that this film might be a little too overcrowded!
I mean, The Avengers worked so well because they all had their personality's established in their solo movies, but quick silver, scarlet witch and vision have not. Besides that, you have to progress with the story and establish Ultron as a badass villain!
It worries me, but the trailer makes it look like the greatest thing ever! And i really like the tone of the trailer, a lot darker than the other marvel movie's tones. but then again, the trailer for iron man 3 was dark and that movie was cheesy and comickbooky as hell!
But hey, im being a pessimist here! hope the movie is great!

The Avengers 2: Age of Ultron trailer dropped last night.  The boys and I are big fans of the superhero genre, and the Marvel Cinematic Universe in particular.

Ultron  was created by Roy Thomas and John Buscema and his first adventure was in Avengers # 54 July 1968. 

The Ultron robot was a project of Dr. Henry Pym (who at the time attended the Avengers as Ant-Man). Ultron's body consists of a variation of Adamantium, metal fictional Marvel Universe virtually indestructible. 

Ultron rebelled against the creator and hypnotized Hulk to attack the Avengers, being given as destroyed in the ensuing fight. After that your program spent perfecting his metal body, which already had several versions. 

Ultron is notable for having created two beings who became powerful Avengers: Vision, a copy of the android body that made the Original Human Torch. And Jocasta, Ultron a female version of himself.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
I have strong feeling this movie will be epic on so many levels. I really enjoyed Ultron storylines in comics (i mean i loved but hated him as villain), though first encounter came to suprisingly anti-climatic solution.
Oh and geek in me and huge Stargate franchise fan loves to see James Spader (known to SG fans as Daniel Jackson from 1994 movie) is playing Ultron. from geek to villain
(warning, possible spoilers ahead of previous marvel movies and comics, so read at your own risk)
i am geniuenly interested, how many connections they plan to make with actual comics. I mean, all we know to date is that Ultron is made by Iron man, not by Hank Pym (also known as Goliath at time of Ultron 1 creation, other more famous aliases include ant-man, giant-man, yellowjacket). I mean Pym (or Janet "winsome wasp" van Dyne) doesnt apparently appear here, which is actually bit sad, but then again, 2 huge brains in same movie (Stark and Pym) would probably be not so good idea, especially as Pym adds more drama. Still, does Stark uses his brainwaves (as Pym did) to map Ultron's brain?
Speaking of changes in roster, compared to first encounter with Ultron (Ultron-5) in comics, Hulk is on roster. Bruce Banner's hulk (i.e not counting Red hulk) was part of avengers only for 3 first issues for years and also Black widow is in team.
What makes this avengers more interesting is that S.H.I.E.L.D disbanded in Captain America: The winter soldier, which should mean that Avengers are now their own team rather than goverment agency, which is quite interesting as in comics it was other way around: Avengers came together after defeating Loki and they were basically independent for certain time.
And now we reach probably one of most interesting parts for me personally- Vision. In comics, Vision was made from body of original Human Torch (not to be confused with Jhonny Storm- Fantastic Four's human torch)- the one that was android. Brain waves used to make Vision's mind were the ones of Simon Williams, power man, who was made as weapon by masters of evil (baron Zemo, enchantress and executioner (latter 2 are asgardians)) to kill avengers, but he had last minute change of heart and saved avengers and died in progress. he was later revived though.
Question here is that since neither android human torch or power man arent even hinted to exist in marvel cinematic universe as of now and if they arent hinted in movie, yet Vision would act same as in comics i.e join avengers against Ultron, it wouldnt be good if it isnt replaced with anything similar. I mean reason why Vision turned to its apparent creator, Ultron (whom he believed created him) was that Vision had brain patterns of power man and some leftover ones of android human torch.
Its also interesting to think wheter or not will Scarlet witch and Vision fall in love in cinematic universe too. descriptions also hint that we may see early hints of Scarlet Witch losing her mind before Avengers disassembled equivelant

In any case, this movie will be interesting.

If anyone cared to read such a long post, then please, discuss with me what do you think

O robô Ultron foi um projeto do Dr. Henry Pym (que na época participava dos Vingadores como Homem-Formiga). O corpo de Ultron é constituído de uma variação de Adamantium, metal fictício do Universo Marvel praticamente indestrutivel.

Ultron rebelou-se contra o criador e hipnotizou Hulk para atacar os Vingadores, sendo dado como destruído na luta que se seguiu. Depois disso seu programa passou a aperfeiçoar seu corpo de metal, que já teve várias versões.

Ultron é notável por ter criado dois seres que se tornaram poderosos Vingadores: o Visão, de uma cópia que fez do corpo andróide do Tocha Humana Original. E Jocasta, uma versão fêmea do próprio Ultron.

Ultron is Tony Stark's creation. He is designed to protect the world. I think the scenes from the trailer that show the robots attacking the compound in the mountains are showing a time when Ultron is good, saving Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch from Baron Von Strucker. Ultron is an artificial intelligence and at some point will have a melt down where he begins to hate the Avengers and humanity, but I think Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch will always be on the side of the Avengers.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
A couple of things to point out in this trailer

#1 - at 0:16 Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch screaming in the crowd

#2 - at 0:37 The avengers in the Avengers tower along with 2 unknown burnette women.  Possibly Maria Hill? Or two women Tony invited just because.... well he's Tony Stark (assuming he broke up with Pepper.......hopefully).

#3 - at 1:02 Possibly Ultron's lair where he upgrades himself?

#4 - at 1:06  Two types of Ultron bots.  Ones with jetpacks, and ones without.... could there be more types? 

#5 at 1:23 Pieces of armor flying at Iron Man similar to his Mark 48 in Iron Man 3.  Also arc reactors on his knees.  Maybe the suit is a combination of multiple suits?  Or simple needs more power to take on the Hulk?

#6 at 1:31 looks a lot like it could be a flash-back sequince with Cap in the 1940's

#7 at 1:33 you can see actor Andy Serkis who is rumored to be playing Ulysses Klaw AKA The Klaw, one of Black Panther's major villains!!!  

#8 at 1:36 ballerinas? Could it be a flash-back for Black Widow?

#9 at 1:39 The shot of Thor grabbing Tony is actually two different scenes.  Note Thor's costume change from him approaching, what we thought was Tony, to him actually grabbing Tony.  Also the two shots are in two different rooms, the second most likely being Avengers tower (windows in the back)

#10 at 1:41 is Hulk getting smarter?  Hulk throws a car, destracting Iron Man and leaving him wide open for Hulk's punch.  Smart move from a bruting hulk huh? (pun intended)

#11 at 1:53 judging by the cracks in the middle of Cap's shield and spreading outwards suggest it was punched?  Cap's shield is stated to be made of vibranium and is indestructible.  So we can assume that the only thing that can damage his shield is..... more vibranium?  The only place you can find more vibranium is in Wakanda, Africa; home of the Black Panther.  

So we got:
Cap's broken shield needing a repair, rumors of The Klaw making an appearance, movie scenes being shot in Africa, and Ultron beings known to upgrade himself with an Adamantium body, another indestructible metal in the comics but cant be used in this movie due to legal rights (thanks Fox).  So Ultron will most likely be coated in vibranium instead...... All this adds up to some major ground work being down for the Black Panther movie!  Maybe we'll get an actual appearance?  Maybe an after credits scene? Who knows....

#12 And FINALLY at 1:56 Ultron looking slightly more human than in the comics, with the Transformer like eyes, and a moving mouth, we can conclude that this villain looks AWESOME and very intimidating...

I cant WAIT for this movie, who's with me?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
WOW,there are some SUPER uneducated people here,so let's clear some stuff up (even though it's public record)
1.James Spader voices and provided some movements for Ultron,film is in post production,so his voice will most likely be tweaked (even though I loved it,)the Pinocchio reference points to the fact that Ultron is part human in a sense due to his programming (which disgusts him) and is no longer "attached to" or controlled by Stark
2.Not only was Quicksilver announced for Avengers:AOU WELL before X-Men:DOFP (it's generally thought that Fox threw a fit at the fact that Disney were able to use him),but Quicksilver's 1st appearence was in The Avengers as was Scarlet Witch,and it wasn't til much later that they were revealed as Mutants
3.this whole "That looks like crap cause I love DC" argument is childish,and in my honest opinion an affront to what you claim to be (if you claim to be a comic book fan that is),If you are a comic book fan then it is NOT a competition,you either love good stories (Every company has some),or you don't and you just jumped on the bandwagon when Hollywood noticed that these films can make money,in which case commenting on the trailer of the follow up to the most successful CBM ever made is probably not the place for you.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
What do you suppose the "main" Ultron will be made of? My guess is Vibranium. He's been made out of pretty much every fictional and real metal imaginable at one point or another.

Yes, Adamantium is the most common, but it hasn't been mentioned at all in this movie universe. Introducing a new concept now (especially in the midst of all the other things they're introducing as well) just seems unnecessary when they could just as easily do Vibrainum. Besides, Vibranium could arguably be an even bigger threat than Adamantium. At least he couldn't absorb energy with Adamantium.

Also, Adamantium is closely tied to the X-Men franchise. Yes, it appears in other comic books, but not nearly as often as X-Men. I wouldn't be surprised if they don't have the rights to use Adamantium.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment: Looks like our worst (or best for some people) thoughts are confirming. Ultron, an android created by Stark Industries goes out of control and develops a God complex and wants to exterminate the human civilization. The conflict with Ultron leaves Tony Stark (slated to appear in Captain America 3 - May 2016) with a moral impact that makes him to create a federal law who will regulate individuals with super powers beacuse of Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch. In the comics, it's called "Civil War" storyline, and appears that events between Age of Ultron and Cap 3 are leading to this. Stark is pro-registration and Rogers not.

70. Verily, We took the covenant of the Children of Israel and sent them Messengers. Whenever there came to them a Messenger with what they themselves desired not - a group of them they called liars, and others among them they killed.

Look how We make the Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) clear to them, yet look how they are deluded away (from the truth).

76. Say (O Muhammad  to mankind): "How do you worship besides Allah something which has no power either to harm or to benefit you? But it is Allah Who is the All-Hearer, All-Knower."

77. Say (O Muhammad ): "O people of the Scripture (Jews and Christians)! 78. Those among the Children of Israel who disbelieved were cursed by the tongue of Dawud (David) and 'Iesa (Jesus), son of Maryam (Mary). That was because they disobeyed (Allah and the Messengers) and were ever transgressing beyond bounds.

79. They used not to forbid one another from the Munkar (wrong, evil-doing, sins, polytheism, disbelief, etc.) which they committed. Vile indeed was what they used to do.

80. You see many of them taking the disbelievers as their Auliya' (protectors and helpers). Evil indeed is that which their ownselves have sent forward before them, for that (reason) Allah's Wrath fell upon them and in torment they will abide.

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
My theory about Ultron's and Hank Pym's origin:
After creating Ultron, Hank Pym showed the A.I. multiple Disney films (his personal favorite being Pinocchio) in hopes it would teach Ultron about humanity and give it a sense of emotions. However, Ultron interpreted them far differently, seeing the quote "I have no strings and now I'm free" as disregarding all morals and others (the strings) to achieve a free world. When Ultron did something truly horrible, Pym felt responsible and ashamed for his actions; thus he shut down Ultron before going into hiding in a desolate location (0:48). Now, after Tony Stark accidentally reawakens Ultron (0:31), the A.I. begins to eradicate the human species to achieve a free world, leaving the Avengers to search for Pym, hoping he has the answer on how to defeat Ultron. 
So, what do you guys think?

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment: !SPOILERS! Ultron's outer armor is usually composed primarily of adamantium, which is almost completely impervious to damage (the first use of the term "adamantium" in Marvel Comics was made in reference to Ultron in Avengers #66, published in July 1969). Most Ultron units are powered by a small internal nuclear furnace and incorporate a "program transmitter" which can beam part or all of Ultron's memory/personality system into other computer systems or duplicate robotic bodies. Ultron can also control other machines remotely. Ultron has occasionally reformed itself with a humanoid appearance above the waist and the appearance of a complex machine, including tractor beam apparatus for flight, below the waist. A later Ultron model developed hive-mind technology, allowing it to animate and control hundreds of other Ultron bodies simultaneously,although only the 'prime' Ultron was composed of adamantium while others were made of steel or secondary adamantium due to the lack of resources to give all the Ultrons adamantium bodies.Ultron also uses an internal molecular rearranger that renders the adamantium components of its workings more malleable and so have the ability to restructure his physical form. What circuitry Ultron has is carefully shielded to protect from damage, although the Scarlet Witch is capable of causing malfunctions with her hex power, Johnny Storm, using his nova burst, managed to damage Ultron's internal circuits while his outer armor remained intact,[47] and Wonder Man was once able to destroy an Ultron by throwing it so hard its internal systems were damaged

He ended up taking on and beating the shit out of the whole catalog of Marvel heroes. The only one capable of stopping him is Dr Strange. It turns out that the berserk Hulk has been under the mind control of Nightmare, Dr Strange's nemesis. The solution is to banish the Hulk to the Crossroads, where he can travel from dimension to dimension in search of a new home.

on her head 1:08

Title: Marvel's "Avengers: Age of Ultron" - Teaser Trailer (OFFICIAL)
Comment:
Marvel has to be really, really careful, how far their going to push this entire franchise thing. You simply can't constantly have such a high output on individual movies, and keep up the quality.
Even worse, you can't keep up a coherent continuity... and in the newer movies, we've already seen first problems in regards of consistency to the entire canon popping up.
I really hope that they won't fall into the same trap as pretty much all larger franchises eventually have fallen into. Because so far, they did a much better job, than any of us could have had expected.

That said:
This trailer looks awesome! And as cynical as I am towards the entire franchise-thing that has more and more become the rule for big blockbuster-movies, I can't deny that this trailer makes me really excited!
